benchmark_config.jira_title: Implement/Test API: GET /1.0/kb/invoiceItems/{invoiceItemId}/auditLogsWithHistory - Retrieve invoice item audit logs with history by id

covered: Valid Request and 200 response with AuditLog objects (TC01)
Empty response 200 with empty array when no logs (TC02)
Not found handling 404 when invoice item does not exist (TC03)
Invalid invoice item ID format returns 400 (TC04)
Authorization checks: 401 for missing or invalid token (TC05, TC06)
Service unavailability 503 when DB is down (TC08)
Handling of large audit log history (TC09) including performance considerations
Regression: presence of required AuditLog fields (TC12)
Concurrency: multiple concurrent requests return 200 and consistent responses (TC14)
Security tests: SQL injection and XSS tests (TC10, TC11)
gaps: Pagination for large datasets is not covered (no explicit pagination tests)
Caching behavior validation (e.g., ETag, Cache-Control headers) is not tested
Authorization scope/403 scenario not covered (only 401 tested)
recommendations: Add explicit pagination tests to verify correct behavior with large datasets and proper paging metadata
Introduce rate limiting/throttling tests to ensure resilience under burst traffic
Add caching-related tests, including ETag and Cache-Control header validation
Include a test for 403 Forbidden to cover insufficient permissions (in addition to 401)
